 quality of life. These programs teach skills that can be applied across many different areas of your life, including academics, and promote optimal functioning, performance and success. You can register for some of these services online; others require a referral from your initial consultation counselor.  Listing of Mind/Body Programs:    Koru Mindfulness Workshops    Self-Compassion Workshop    Trauma-Informed Yoga Group    Biofeedback Services            Services    Back to main content           What to Expect    Individual Counseling    Group Therapy    Couples Counseling    Mind Body Services     Koru Mindfulness Workshops    Self-Compassion Workshop    Trauma-Informed Yoga Group    Biofeedback Services      Psychiatry and Integrative Medicine    Outreach Services and Programs    Peer Support Network                  UIC Logo        Counseling Center          Contact   UIC Counseling Center  1200 West Harrison Street, 2010 SSB, (MC 333), Chicago, Illinois 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3490  Fax: (312) 996-7645        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 